<subSubSection id="C3776556ED643800FC9AFE55FB57FE38" pageId="565" pageNumber="566" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED643800FC9AFE55FB57FE38" blockId="565.[810,1452,173,2070]" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED643800FC9AFE55FC25FE74" bold="true" box="[863,992,411,437]" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B919EACFED643800FCAAFE73FC64FE16" box="[879,929,445,471]" italics="true" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">glob</emphasis>
(=a ball), referring the spherical body of the adult female of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556ED643802FC9AFDCFFEBBF8C4" lastPageId="567" lastPageNumber="568" pageId="565" pageNumber="566" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED643800FC9AFDCFFBC6FC14" blockId="565.[810,1452,173,2070]" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">
<emphasis id="B919EACFED643800FC9AFDCFFB99FDDA" bold="true" box="[863,1116,513,539]" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FB71FDCFFA80FDDD" box="[1204,1349,513,540]" captionStart="FIGURE 379" captionStartId="566.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[205,1340,212,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-19@566.[197,1390,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="566" captionText="FIGURE 379. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, ventral; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum, dorsal; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C–E, H, 0.05 mm; F. G, I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592072/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 379A, B</figureCitation>
) swollen with almost spherical brood pouch; body length 3.03 mm in dissected specimen. Prosome obscurely divided by 4 constrictions or wrinkles demarcating cephalosome and metasome; cephalosome small, narrower than anterior pedigerous somites. Fourthpedigerous somite (brood pouch) extremely expanded, spherical, 2.02×1.89 mm. Urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FC26FD21FB9FFCC8" box="[995,1114,751,777]" captionStart="FIGURE 379" captionStartId="566.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[205,1340,212,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-19@566.[197,1390,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="566" captionText="FIGURE 379. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, ventral; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum, dorsal; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C–E, H, 0.05 mm; F. G, I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592072/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 379C</figureCitation>
) rudimentary, very small, 2- segmented: first urosomite short, notarticulated from prosome, with traces of 2 or 3 suture lines on surface; second urosomite narrowing posteriorly. Caudal rami completely fused to anal somite, wider than long and narrowing distally, unarmed but ornamented with minute setules on surfaces.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED643800FC9AFC10FAE2FAE8" blockId="565.[810,1452,173,2070]" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FC0AFC13FBA6FC39" box="[975,1123,989,1016]" captionStart="FIGURE 379" captionStartId="566.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[205,1340,212,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-19@566.[197,1390,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="566" captionText="FIGURE 379. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, ventral; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum, dorsal; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C–E, H, 0.05 mm; F. G, I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592072/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 379D, E</figureCitation>
) large, 135×85 μm, tapering, bluntly tipped, with minute spinules on ventral surface. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FC7DFBEFFBF7FBFA" box="[952,1074,1057,1083]" captionStart="FIGURE 379" captionStartId="566.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[205,1340,212,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-19@566.[197,1390,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="566" captionText="FIGURE 379. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, ventral; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum, dorsal; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C–E, H, 0.05 mm; F. G, I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592072/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 379F</figureCitation>
) 71×83 μm, shortand broad, leaf-like, with 3 partial sutures (or constrictions) along posterior surface, armed distally with 5 or 6 small setae, ornamented with minute spinules on all surfaces. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FC52FB67FBCEFB02" box="[919,1035,1193,1219]" captionStart="FIGURE 379" captionStartId="566.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[205,1340,212,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-19@566.[197,1390,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="566" captionText="FIGURE 379. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, ventral; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum, dorsal; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C–E, H, 0.05 mm; F. G, I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592072/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 379G</figureCitation>
) stout, 3-segmented; coxa very short; basis 66×54 μm, unarmed; unsegmentedendopod much narrowerthan proximal segments, 50×31 μm; armed with 1 smallseta distally plus small terminal claw.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDED643802FC9AFAFFFD06FA37" blockId="565.[810,1452,173,2070]" lastBlockId="567.[136,778,1363,1968]" lastPageId="567" lastPageNumber="568" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FC1DFAFFFB98FA8D" box="[984,1117,1329,1356]" captionStart="FIGURE 379" captionStartId="566.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[205,1340,212,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-19@566.[197,1390,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="566" captionText="FIGURE 379. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, ventral; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum, dorsal; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C–E, H, 0.05 mm; F. G, I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592072/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 379H</figureCitation>
) broad, bilobate at each posterolateral corner, outer posterolateral lobe fringed with fine spinules along distal margin; ornamented with patch of minute spinules in mid ventral surface. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FC62FA77FBD6FA15" box="[935,1043,1465,1492]" captionStart="FIGURE 379" captionStartId="566.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[205,1340,212,1831]" captionTargetId="figure-19@566.[197,1390,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="566" captionText="FIGURE 379. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, habitus, right; C, urosome, ventral; D, cephalic region, ventral; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum, dorsal; I, mandible. Scale bars: A, B, 0.5 mm; C–E, H, 0.05 mm; F. G, I, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592072/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 379I</figureCitation>
) with coxal gnathobase broadening out towards oblique medial margin; margin serrate, with protruded proximal, pectinate part: palp reduced and unsegmented, with small, outer knob (vestige of exopod) in middle, bearing 1 or 2 minute setae; distal half (endopodal region) narrowing, bearing 2 small subdistal setae on medial margin, 2 or 3 minute setae apically; with few small spinules on medial surface. Maxillule consisting of precoxa and palp: precoxa (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FB32F904FAAEF925" box="[1271,1387,1738,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 380" captionStartId="567.[136,245,1227,1253]" captionTargetBox="[168,1430,228,1172]" captionTargetId="figure-18@567.[136,1451,202,1193]" captionTargetPageId="567" captionText="FIGURE 380. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, precoxa of maxillule; B, palp of maxillule; C, maxilla; D, maxilliped; E, leg 1; F, leg 2; G, leg 5 pair. Scale bars: A–F, 0.02 mm; G, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592074" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592074/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 380A</figureCitation>
) with patch of minute setules proximally and bearing 3 strong, spiniform teeth on mediodistal arthrite: palp (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FAF5F8C0FA61F8E9" box="[1328,1444,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 380" captionStartId="567.[136,245,1227,1253]" captionTargetBox="[168,1430,228,1172]" captionTargetId="figure-18@567.[136,1451,202,1193]" captionTargetPageId="567" captionText="FIGURE 380. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, precoxa of maxillule; B, palp of maxillule; C, maxilla; D, maxilliped; E, leg 1; F, leg 2; G, leg 5 pair. Scale bars: A–F, 0.02 mm; G, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592074" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592074/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 380B</figureCitation>
) distally bilobed; outer lobe (exopod) with 2 smallsetae apically and 3 small spinules subdistally; inner lobe (basis+endopod) broad, with 1 large seta subdistally on medial margin and 4 tubercles apically, 3 outer tubercles each tipped with 1 small seta. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED643800FACDF876FABAF813" box="[1288,1407,1976,2002]" captionStart="FIGURE 380" captionStartId="567.[136,245,1227,1253]" captionTargetBox="[168,1430,228,1172]" captionTargetId="figure-18@567.[136,1451,202,1193]" captionTargetPageId="567" captionText="FIGURE 380. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, precoxa of maxillule; B, palp of maxillule; C, maxilla; D, maxilliped; E, leg 1; F, leg 2; G, leg 5 pair. Scale bars: A–F, 0.02 mm; G, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592074" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592074/files/figure.png" pageId="565" pageNumber="566">Fig. 380C</figureCitation>
) 4- segmented, consistingof syncoxa, basis, and 2-segmented endopod; syncoxawith 1 seta medially; basis drawn out to massive, curved claw bearing 1 seta proximally and 2 rows of denticles along distal part of convex proximal margin; endopod small, with broad seta on first segment and 1 broad and 2 small setae on second. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58ED663802FD19FA77FF0DFA37" captionStart="FIGURE 380" captionStartId="567.[136,245,1227,1253]" captionTargetBox="[168,1430,228,1172]" captionTargetId="figure-18@567.[136,1451,202,1193]" captionTargetPageId="567" captionText="FIGURE 380. Contoura globosa gen. et sp. nov., female. A, precoxa of maxillule; B, palp of maxillule; C, maxilla; D, maxilliped; E, leg 1; F, leg 2; G, leg 5 pair. Scale bars: A–F, 0.02 mm; G, 0.05 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592074" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592074/files/figure.png" pageId="567" pageNumber="568">Fig. 380D</figureCitation>
) represented by small lobe tipped with 1 seta
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655ED673803FF4DF8BDFD92F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4592072" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4592072" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4592072/files/figure.png" pageId="566" pageNumber="567" startId="566.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[205,1340,212,1831]" targetPageId="566">
